The performance of RE methods significantly impacts the quality of {{2111.13611_FO0100||FO}} as well as the RE coverage of documents. Although we used state-of-the-art commercial APIs, these nonetheless struggle on open web documents. To illustrate this, we randomly sampled {{2111.13611_FO0101||FO}} documents from DoCo and compared the count of RE tuples returned by Diffbot/Rosette against the count by a human relation extractor. Diffbot returned {{2111.13611_FO0102||FO}} fewer relational tuples, and Rosette returned {{2111.13611_FO0103||FO}} fewer, suggesting the need for further improvement of RE methods.